\"panel-grid panel-no-style\">\r\n<div id=\"pgc-149-0-0\" class=\"panel-grid-cell\" data-weight=\"1\">\r\n<div id=\"panel-149-0-0-0\" class=\"so-panel widget widget_sow-editor panel-first-child panel-last-child\" data-index=\"0\" data-style=\"{&quot;background_display&quot;:&quot;tile&quot;}\">\r\n<div class=\"so-widget-sow-editor so-widget-sow-editor-base\">\r\n<div class=\"siteorigin-widget-tinymce textwidget\">\r\n<div class=\"siteorigin-widget-tinymce textwidget\">\r\n\r\nBuilding Rich content is enabled through \"Site Origin\" graphic framework .\r\n\r\n\"Page Builder\" allows to control the blog area into rows and columns with special widget attached to each row-column,. SiteOrigin\'s PageBuilder Tab selected from  the top right tab of blog Editor, allows to Add Rows and attach widgets with content from repository or through composition.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\nA new post can be edited in three modes - Visual, Text or Page Builder. The control panels in each mode address different format, style and use of controls.\r\n\r\n<strong>Visual View</strong>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-190 size-large\" src=\"http://96.67.213.65/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/VisualView-1024x143.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"525\" height=\"73\" />\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>Text View</strong>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-191 size-large\" src=\"http://96.67.213.65/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/TextView-1024x77.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"525\" height=\"39\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>PageBuilder View</strong>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-192 size-large\" src=\"http://96.67.213.65/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/PageBuilderView-1024x44.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"525\" height=\"23\" />\r\n\r\nThe Page or Post Creation is helped by Editor which allows to layout the panel area into rows and columns. “Add Row” allows to add a row with specified number of columns of desired/variables size. Each of the layout area can include different UI widgets. Further Pages can include Posts and Post can Include Pages.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-169 size-large\" src=\"http://96.67.213.65/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/a1_1-1024x172.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"525\" height=\"88\" />\r\n\r\nTo add the content, the widget with name “SiteOrigin Editor” can be selected to start editing rich text content. Many other widgets allow creating rich content.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-170 size-large\" src=\"http://96.67.213.65/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/a1_2-1024x377.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"525\" height=\"193\" />\r\n\r\nWidgets on Left Panel are classified into Groups of controls:\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Ultimate Addon Bundle: Mainly to organize contents into multiple tabs.</li>\r\n 	<li>Widgets Bundle: Widgets such as Button, Contact Form, Editor, Features, GoogleMaps, Image, Post Carousel, Slider, Tabs, Taxonomy</li>\r\n 	<li>Page Builder Widgets: Layout Builder, Post Content, Post Loop</li>\r\n 	<li>WordPress Widgets: Archives, Calendar, Categories, Meta, Navigation Menu, Pages, RSS, Search and other External World Blog Posting related widgets</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<div class=\"siteorigin-widget-tinymce textwidget\">\r\n<div class=\"siteorigin-widget-tinymce textwidget\">\r\n\r\nFor more  details refer to:   <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=pLXWud03dFk\">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=pLXWud03dFk</a>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>','Article Content Builder','','inherit','closed','closed','','149-autosave-v1','','','2018-03-13 01:11:24','2018-03-13 09:11:24','',149,'http://96.67.213.65/index.php/2018/03/13/149-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(195,2,'2018-03-13 01:24:49','2018-03-13 09:24:49','<ul>\r\n 	<li>A Table-Press DataSet is created through import of CSV file. The following steps may be executed to use the file upload content in the Article.\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>The following Menu (“TablePress”) on the left Panel allows to create tables normally or through importwith data in different formats (CSV, HTML,JSON, XLS, XLSX): <img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-171\" src=\"http://96.67.213.65/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/a1_3_1-135x300.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"135\" height=\"300\" /><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-172 size-large\" src=\"http://96.67.213.65/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/a1_3_2-1024x549.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"525\" height=\"281\" /></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Just Select the TablePress Icon on the Editor  with tool tip \"Insert a Table from TablePress\"  and select the newly created table - \"Insert Short Code\" Button on the Panel.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-173 size-large\" src=\"http://96.67.213.65/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/a1_4-1024x151.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"525\" height=\"77\" />\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-147\" src=\"http://96.67.213.65/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/Screen-6-1-300x244.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"244\" /><span style=\"font-size: 1rem;\">This will generate the following table instance with Short code embedded link:</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<div style=\"width: 50%;\">[table id=2 /]</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Now on the Right Panel, Operations, \"Save\" / \"Preview\"/\"Sub to WorkFlow\"/\"Publish\" can be performed as desired.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-145\" src=\"http://96.67.213.65/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/Screen-7-281x300.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"281\" height=\"300\" />\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','File Upload - Table Press CSV Import Table','','inherit','closed','closed','','143-autosave-v1','','','2018-03-13 01:24:49','2018-03-13 09:24:49','',143,'http://96.67.213.65/index.php/2018/03/13/143-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(196,2,'2018-03-13 01:39:38','2018-03-13 09:39:38','Workflows in the KMT (Knowledge Management Tool) are restricted to only “1-worflow” at present. The workflow can be deleted and re-created as per the new/changed requirements. Workflow can be defined to dynamically review the publish process before the “Knowledge Content” blog is published to the world. The left side panel, workflow allows to edit the workflow and set validity.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-174 size-large\" src=\"http://96.67.213.65/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/a1_5-1024x435.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"525\" height=\"223\" />\r\n\r\nWorkflow also allows to customize the rules as required. At each workflow step level, it is possible to configure the next step together with a custom eMail definition to process.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-164 size-full\" src=\"http://96.67.213.65/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/a4_2.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"820\" height=\"712\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>Trigger escalation processes (e.g., automated emails/texts to approvers, reminders) for lifecycle activities</strong>\r\n\r\nThe Workflow InBox – shows the workflow dynamics as workflows are delegated. Inbox in workflows right panel menu shows the Work delegated.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-165 size-full\" src=\"http://96.67.213.65/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/a5_1.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"1884\" height=\"281\" />\r\n\r\nWorkflow Setting contains Email Tab to configure the Email settings:\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-166 size-full\" src=\"http://96.67.213.65/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/a5_2.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"450\" height=\"71\" />\r\n\r\nThe escalation frequency of intimation can be set through the following settings:\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-167 size-full\" src=\"http://96.67.213.65/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/a5_3.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"1501\" height=\"793\" />\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>Article Submission to Workflow</strong>\r\n\r\nIt is possible to define who all can submit the created content to the workflow and also the type of post.\r\n\r\nWorkflow after “create” and “save”, followed by “Activate” workflow from “Workflow” settings, will become available next to publish button on the Right panel with button label “Submit to Workflow”.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-197 size-full\" src=\"http://96.67.213.65/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/Workflow_three_in_one.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"862\" height=\"285\" />\r\n\r\nOnce the workflow is submitted, it the history can be tracked through “Workflow History” on the left menu panel.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-178 size-large\" src=\"http://96.67.213.65/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/a1_7-1024x163.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"525\" height=\"84\" />\r\n\r\nFor more details, please refer to the following video clip: <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=_R2uVWQicsM\">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=_R2uVWQicsM</a>','Article Publish Workflow','','publish','open','open','','article-publish-workflow','','','2018-03-13 03:52:38','2018-03-13 11:52:38','',0,'http://96.67.213.65/?p=196',0,'post','',0),(197,2,'2018-03-13 01:34:00','2018-03-13 09:34:00','','Workflow_three_in_one','','inherit','open','closed','','workflow_three_in_one','','','2018-03-13 01:34:16','2018-03-13 09:34:16','',196,'http://96.67.213.65/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/Workflow_three_in_one.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(198,2,'2018-03-13 03:52:44','2018-03-13 11:52:44','Workflows in the KMT (Knowledge Management Tool) are restricted to only “1-worflow” at present. The workflow can be deleted and re-created as per the new/changed requirements. Workflow can be defined to dynamically review the publish process before the “Knowledge Content” blog is published to the world. The left side panel, workflow allows to edit the workflow and set validity.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-174 size-large\" src=\"http://96.67.213.65/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/a1_5-1024x435.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"525\" height=\"223\" />\r\n\r\nWorkflow also allows to customize the rules as required. At each workflow step level, it is possible to configure the next step together with a custom eMail definition to process.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-164 size-full\" src=\"http://96.67.213.65/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/a4_2.png